I"ä<p>To install it in ubuntu : <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/docs/installation/ubuntu/">Installation</a>.</p>

<h2 id="create-a-jekyll">create a jekyll</h2>

<p>to create a basic website</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>jekyll new websiteName
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="jekyll-with-no-theme">jekyll with no theme</h3>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>jekyll new websiteName <span class="nt">--blank</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>then create a Gemfile</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>bundle init
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>then in this file add jekyll</p>
<div class="language-ruby highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">gem</span> <span class="s2">"jekyll"</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="_configyml">_config.yml</h2>

<p>this file contains configuration &amp; global variables.</p>

<p>After each modification of this file, we need to restart the server</p>

<h2 id="_includes">_includes</h2>

<p>contains HTML for elements youâ€™d repeatedly use like header, footer, navbar, â€¦</p>

<h2 id="_layouts">_layouts</h2>

<p>contains templates for different types of pages.</p>

<p>in this directory store all the layout like default.html</p>

<p>to use them, in the front matter :</p>
<div class="language-yml highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nn">---</span>
<span class="na">layout</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">default</span>
<span class="na">title</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">Home</span>
<span class="nn">---</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="_posts">_posts</h2>

<p>contains .md and .html blog posts</p>

<h2 id="_sass">_sass</h2>

<p>contains styling for website</p>

<p>can contains multiple sass files</p>

<h3 id="include-multiple-sass">include multiple sass</h3>

<p>in assets/css/main.scss</p>
<div class="language-scss highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="na">---</span><span class="err"> 
</span><span class="na">---</span><span class="err"> 

$</span><span class="na">baseurl</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s2">"main"</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s2">"utilities"</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="nc">...</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>list all sass files contained in _sass</p>

<h2 id="start-server">start server</h2>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>bundle <span class="nb">exec </span>jekyll serve
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="add-collection">add collection</h2>

<p>to add a new collection we add to _config.yml</p>
<div class="language-yml highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>    <span class="na">collections</span><span class="pi">:</span>
      <span class="na">recipes</span><span class="pi">:</span>
        <span class="na">output</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="no">true</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>where recipes is the name of our collection</p>

<p>output true, so all the items of our collection will be a page linkable</p>

<h2 id="debug">debug</h2>

<p>to inspect a variable like with console_log or var_dump :</p>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>nil 
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>ou</p>
<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>null 
</code></pre></div></div>
